joescreen-rooms is NOT deployed to production yet — it needs a public LiveKit SFU that does not
exist at time of writing (apps/livekit is shipped dark: no hosted URL, DNS, TLS, or API key/secret).

Deploying it now would publish a rooms.cheffing.dev that hands out invite links pointing at no SFU,
with presence + browser-watch non-functional.

The CI deploy workflow (.github/workflows/cloudflare-deploy-prod.yml) skips any worker dir that
contains this .deploy-disabled marker.

To ENABLE deploy (once the SFU is up):
  1. Deploy apps/livekit on a real host with a domain + TLS + a fresh LIVEKIT API key/secret.
  2. Set LIVEKIT_URL (wss://…) and LIVEKIT_API_URL (https://…) in wrangler.jsonc (production env).
  3. wrangler secret put --env production LIVEKIT_API_KEY   (and LIVEKIT_API_SECRET) — for presence
     + browser view-only tokens.
  4. Delete this file and push. CI will deploy rooms.cheffing.dev.
The ROOMS KV namespace is already provisioned (id in wrangler.jsonc), so no KV step is needed.
